text: Alavieska is a municipality in Northern Ostrobothnia, Finland. As of 31 December 2023, 2,435 people lived there. Neighbouring municipalities are Kalajoki, Merijärvi, Oulainen and Ylivieska. It was founded in 1879. One of the [main] rivers is Kalajoki river.https://yle.fi/a/74-20083223.
